msgid ""
"When creating a bond, the UI will display a management IP address in the "
"private network 127.x.x.1/32. This IP address is used solely for managing"
" the bond and is not involved in traffic forwarding. Once the bond device"
" is created, you can assign an IP address and a firewall zone to it. "
"Please note that bond configuration is not editable after creation. If "
"you need to modify the bond's IP address or zone, you'll have to remove "
"its configuration and reconfigure it again. If you need to change bond "
"devices, bond mode or management IP you'll have to remove bond "
"configuration and bond device and recreate it from scratch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:88 0eb64b8579be4f029e1cfeb238846630
msgid "VLAN"
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:90 5da3e39c60ca449ea89c990848fa59f1
msgid ""
"A VLAN, or Virtual Local Area Network, is a network technology that "
"allows network administrators to create logically segmented networks "
"within a physical network infrastructure. VLANs enable the creation of "
"multiple broadcast domains in a network, even though they are physically "
"connected to the same network switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:92 f81256dfdbc246cfa614a3d114cd034f
msgid ""
"You can create a new VLAN device by clicking the :guilabel:`Create VLAN "
"device` button. Select the VLAN device type:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:95 3f2cf6e906ee4fe8a122e492d2be2d0a
msgid ""
"VLAN 802.1q is primarily used for standard VLAN implementations within "
"organizations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:96 e0fdf1357daa49ea9af64b21c345afd7
msgid ""
"802.1ad (QinQ) is used in service provider networks where multiple "
"customers require VLAN segmentation, and these segmented VLANs need to be"
" transported across the provider's network"
msgstr ""

#: ../../network.rst:99 cc623ad171f544e280319abe15b5a1e4
msgid ""
"Make sure also to chose correct VLAN ID. Please bear in mind that you "
"must setup the same VLAN ID inside the network switch."
msgstr ""

